   <apex:pageBlockSection title="1. How do I use SCI for tracking evals within Salesfoce.com?" columns="1">
 
       <br></br>
       For each eval you execute at the custome site, please create a new SCI for that opportunity. Choose One of the following under the 'Type of Interaction' Field <br></br>
         - Security Preview <br></br> 
         - POC Shared <br></br>
         - POC Inline <br></br>
       If the interaction type is a POC Inline, you can initiate a provisioning request from the SCI itself. 
       
   </apex:pageBlockSection>
    
   <apex:pageBlockSection title="2. How do I track progress for Inline POCs?" columns="1">
       <br></br>
       - If your SCI is of the type 'POC Inline', please use the 'POC Phases' section of the SCI page layout to track progress. <br></br>
       - Create the appropriate phases as your POC Proceeds. Not all Phases will be needed for each POC.<br></br>
       - You can create activities and attach documents under each Phase.<br></br>
   </apex:pageBlockSection>
   <apex:pageBlockSection title="3. What happens to my old Eval Notes?" columns="1"> 
       <br></br>
       - For existing Eval notes, an SCI record with an appropriate Interaction Type has been created.<br></br>
       - Where applicable, You can access the legacy eval notes from an SCI using the 'Evaluation progress Notes (Legacy) Link'.<br></br>
       - If you don't see an SCI for an Eval in progress, please create one with the appropriate interaction type.<br></br>
   </apex:pageBlockSection>
